Using dynamic table macro with our confluence 3.0.1 generates the following error message:

Error formatting macro: dynamictable: com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.ConversionException: Invalid final field java.util.Collections$SynchronizedCollection.c ---- Debugging information ---- message : Invalid final field java.util.Collections$SynchronizedCollection.c line number : 23 path : /com.revere.confluence.dynamictable.model.Table/rows/java.util.Collections-SynchronizedCollection/default/c cause-message : Invalid final field java.util.Collections$SynchronizedCollection.c class : com.revere.confluence.dynamictable.model.Table cause-exception : com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.reflection.ObjectAccessException required-type : java.util.Collections$SynchronizedRandomAccessList -------------------------------
header1 	header2 	header3

The code on the page: 
{code}
{dynamictable:TableNametet|title=adfg Table Title}
     |header1|header2|header3|
{dynamictable}
{code}

Both new pages and old ones ( that were created under Confluence 2.7.1 and previous java versions ) are having this issue.

I have seen a similar issue: http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-4082

We have a large nuber of pages using this plugin, and we do not want to lose this plugin with our upgrade from 2.7.1 to 3.0.1 Confluence.

